Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas announced on Thursday at the UN General Assembly session that he would break all agreements with Israel if the future government of that country tried to comply with Benjamin Netanyahu's announcement of the annexation of the occupied Palestinian countries.
"If the future Government of Israel, which will arise, comes to the realization of this plan, we will invalidate all signed agreements (with Israel) and withdraw from all commitments made," he announced.
