Make sure you wash your hands well
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. after coming home or before meals).
But not everyone knows that to actually get rid of the germs, you have to do it properly.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30 to 40 seconds for washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
But most of us wash them more quickly!
Just warm water and regular soap – it is not true that it has to be antibacterial (many doctors even advise them).
By washing, we wipe not only the bottoms and the tops of the hand, but also: fingertips (jointed or single) – rub them with colossal movements with the inside of the other hand, the space between the fingers (put your hands together, wipe your fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb is covered with the other hand and in such a volume we turn it to the right and left for a moment.
In an emergency situation (when hands cannot be washed), we should wipe our hands with a wet handkerchief and then use antibacterial gel (in drugs, from 5 zł).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the door or door with your hands washed (the recommendation of the General Inspectorate of Sanitation).
Open it with a paper towel.
