He stated that he had met with American diplomats because he had been inspired by France, Germany and the United Kingdom.
However, he stressed that Iran would not take up talks in the atmosphere of "maximum pressure".
"And even if we want to negotiate with Americans in 5+1 format, no one can predict what the final result will be," Rowhani said.
The day before, the Iranian leader said that he did not exclude talks from the US, and to the European parties to the nuclear agreement, he rejected US sanctions on Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran following the US withdrawal from the nuclear agreement "are a precondition which does not allow" for dialogue.
If we can overcome this precondition and if America lifts sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America – he declared.
He added that he did not exclude a meeting with US President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a conversation in the coming week at the UN General Assembly.
Trump: "Iran asked, I said no."
Donald Trump wrote on Twitter that he rejected the request of the Iranian side.
"Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said "no!" was tweeted by the President of the United States.
Voltage with nuclear agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease the tension between Washington and Tehran in some way to save the 2015 agreement with Iran, which they were signatories to.
In exchange for lifting Iran's economic sanctions, the nuclear weapons programme will be abandoned and the nuclear sector will be subject to the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the withdrawal of the US from the agreement in May 2015, the remaining signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to maintain the agreement in force.
So far, none of this has worked out.
Washington is using the strategy of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iran's oil.
Tehran announced that if it did not receive a permit to export raw material, it would limit its obligations every 60 days as a result of the agreement.
