The Act on the Publicity of the Property of the Families of the Most Important State Officials, whose project was established in the Office of the Prime Minister, was adopted by the Sejm on 11 September.
The provisions provide that, inter alia, the Prime Minister, Ministers, Members, Members of the EP, Senators, Presidents: the Constitutional Court, the General Administrative Court and the Supreme Court, as well as the persons at the head of other State institutions, will be obliged to include in the property statement information on the personal property of spouses, children and persons in common use.
